  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Edmund Quincy refers to a letter he received from May Hill of Pawtucket, which he sent to Maria Weston Chapman. He now sends a paragraph from Ray Potter&apos;s Anti-Sectarian on the same subject. He supposes that &quot;these Atonements narrowness originated among his little set of whom Sophia [Louise] Little is one.&quot; He thinks that Maria W. Chapman should write something on the Non-Resistance platform &quot;apropos to this letter and paragraph.&quot; He makes recommendations about appointing a Committee of Arrangements for the Non-Resistance meetings; Edmund Quincy thinks all the meetings should be held in the Chardon Street Chapel.</subfield>
